## CRITICAL BUG FIX: Team-relative role assignment

### The Bug
Tournament uses 4-agent and 8-agent maps with split teams:
- 4 agents: [0,0,1,1] (2v2), [0,0,0,1] (3v1), [0,1,1,1] (1v3)
- 8 agents: [0,0,1,1,1,1,1,1] (2v6), [0,0,0,0,0,0,1,1] (6v2)

Role assignment used GLOBAL agent IDs with fixed priorities:
- _SCRAMBLER_PRIORITY = (3, 7, 6, 2)
- _ALIGNER_PRIORITY = (0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7)

With 3 agents (IDs 0,1,2): agent 3 not on team → no scrambler assigned correctly
  but ALL 3 become aligners → NO MINERS → economy collapse!
With 1 agent (ID 3): becomes pure scrambler → 0 alignment score!

### The Fix
- Added shared_team_ids set to track which agent IDs are on our team
- _desired_role now filters priority lists to team members only
- Ensures proper role distribution regardless of which global IDs we control

